# tursas

Tursas is a simple chess engine implemented in Clojure.

## Status

- UCI / XBoard interface : some stubbs exist
- Saving / Loading game state: done
- REPL to play with: stubbs, not connected to state handling yet
- State representation with 0x88 board: done
- Move generation: done
- Search algorithm: wip
- Evaluator: simple, material balance for now

## Usage

Currently this is un-usable. It is very much work in progress code.

## Installation

Use leiningen to build the project.
lein uberjar

Then you can run the generated jar file to access the engine.

